markdownRemark.html:
Since my last post, I was fortunate enough to complete an internship at LinkedIn and graduate from Georgia Tech. That pretty much sums it up, along with great memories along the way. But suffice to say the least, it’s been one wild ride, from COVID-19 impacting the economy, to graduating virtually from one of the top technical institutes in the nation.

As much as I didn’t like the assignments and all-nighters I had to pull for assignments and exams, I’m starting to feel a bit of Stockholm Syndrome creep into my system.

frontmatter.description: It's been a while. Read this post to see how I reflected on this past year of events, and how I plan for future events.
frontmatter.title: I just graduated. What's next?
